{
  "local_port": 35932,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get free website?",
  "response": "Getting a free website is possible, and there are several methods to do this depending on your needs and technical skills. Here\u2019s a guide to help you:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Use Free Website Builders**\nThese platforms allow you to create a website without coding, often with drag-and-drop tools. However, most free plans come with limitations, such as ads or a subdomain.\n\n- **Wix**: Free plan with Wix-branded ads and a subdomain (e.g., yoursite.wixsite.com).\n- **Weebly**: Free plan with basic features and Weebly branding.\n- **WordPress.com**: Free plan with WordPress branding and a subdomain (e.g., yoursite.wordpress.com).\n- **Strikingly**: Free plan for single-page websites.\n- **Google Sites**: Free and simple website builder for basic sites.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Get a Free Subdomain**\nSome platforms offer free subdomains as part of their free plans. Keep in mind that these domains may look less professional (e.g., yoursite.exampledomain.com).\n\n- Examples: Wix, WordPress.com, Blogger.\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Use Open-Source CMS with Free Hosting**\nFor more control, you can use open-source platforms like WordPress.org, Joomla, or Drupal and pair them with free hosting services.\n\n- **Free Hosting Providers**:\n  - InfinityFree\n  - 000webhost\n  - FreeHostingNoAds\n- Note: Free hosting often has limitations like ads, limited storage, or slower speeds.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Leverage GitHub Pages**\nIf you\u2019re comfortable with coding or want to learn, GitHub Pages offers free hosting for static websites. You can even use a custom domain for free.\n\n- Steps:\n  1. Create a GitHub account.\n  2. Upload your HTML/CSS/JavaScript files to a repository.\n  3. Enable GitHub Pages for the repository.\n  4. Access your site at `https://username.github.io/repositoryname`.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Use Free Website Templates**\nMany platforms offer free templates that you can customize for your website.\n\n- Sources:\n  - HTML5 UP\n  - Start Bootstrap\n  - ThemeForest (some free themes)\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Consider Free Trials**\nSome premium website builders and hosting providers offer free trials (e.g., Squarespace, Wix Premium). Use these to test their features, but be prepared to pay after the trial ends.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **Look for Student or Non-Profit Discounts**\nIf you\u2019re a student or part of a non-profit organization, you may qualify for free or discounted website services.\n\n- Examples:\n  - GitHub Student Developer Pack\n  - Google for Nonprofits\n\n---\n\n### Things to Keep in Mind:\n- **Ads and Branding**: Free plans often include ads or branding from the platform.\n- **Limitations**: Free plans may have limited storage, bandwidth, or features.\n- **Custom Domain**: To look professional, you may need to purchase a custom domain (e.g., yoursite.com).\n\nBy choosing the right method, you can create a free website that suits your needs!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
